17/05/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The Kosovo parliament approved the appointment of the country's first constitutional judges on Friday (May 15th), media reported. 
They include four Albanians, a Serb, and a Turk. 
Kosovo's constitutional court will have a total of nine judges. 
The remaining three judges will be foreigners, named by Peter Feith, head of the International Civilian Office (ICO) in Kosovo. 
The judges will have a nine-year mandate without the possibility of renewal, while the head of the Constitutional Court will be elected with the votes of the judges. 
(Kosovo Times, Balkan Insight, Beta, B92 - 15/05/09)
